  38: /**
  39:  * A client-side HTTP request.
  40:  * <p>
  41:  * Instances are created by an {@link WebClient} instance, via one of the methods corresponding to the specific
  42:  * HTTP methods such as {@link WebClient#get}, etc...
  43:  * <p>
  44:  * The request shall be configured prior sending, the request is immutable and when a mutator method
  45:  * is called, a new request is returned allowing to expose the request in a public API and apply further customization.
  46:  * <p>
  47:  * After the request has been configured, the methods
  48:  * <ul>
  49:  *   <li>{@link #send()}</li>
  50:  *   <li>{@link #sendStream(ReadStream)}</li>
  51:  *   <li>{@link #sendJson(Object)} ()}</li>
  52:  *   <li>{@link #sendForm(MultiMap)}</li>
  53:  * </ul>
  54:  * can be called.
  55:  * The {@code sendXXX} methods perform the actual request, they can be called multiple times to perform the same HTTP
  56:  * request at different points in time.
  57:  * <p>
  58:  * The handler is called back with
  59:  * <ul>
  60:  *   <li>an {@link HttpResponse} instance when the HTTP response has been received</li>
  61:  *   <li>a failure when the HTTP request failed (like a connection error) or when the HTTP response could
  62:  *   not be obtained (like connection or unmarshalling errors)</li>
  63:  * </ul>
  64:  * <p>
  65:  * Most of the time, this client will buffer the HTTP response fully unless a specific {@link BodyCodec} is used
  66:  * such as {@link BodyCodec#create(Handler)}.
  67:  *
  68:  * @param <T> the type of response body
  69:  * @author <a href="mailto:julien@julienviet.com">Julien Viet</a>
  70:  */
  71: @VertxGen
  72: public interface HttpRequest<T> {
  73: 
  74:   /**
  75:    * Configure the request to use a new method {@code value}.
  76:    *
  77:    * @return a reference to this, so the API can be used fluently
  78:    */
  79:   @Fluent
  
